Description: Fragmen t of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine light pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 26 Name Archokrates. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.18266.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0877)
